      "body" : "`github-merge.py` already refuses to merge if there are any conflicts, so in principle this should already be the case for top-level merges.\r\n\r\nI do think it should be possible for non-top-level merges (so those part of pull requests). Merges with conflict resolve exist for a good reason, and I don't think the use of git to accomplish development tasks (as well as convenience for contributors) should be unnecessarily restricted for paranoia reasons.",
